Python Command-Line tools for ClamAV (clamTools)
================================================

TOOLS:
------

 * (clamTools):
       - clamTools.py - Tool for update signatures, scan & view logs/quarantine.
 * (clamToolsdbd):
       - clamToolsdbd.py: Daemon to update Sanesecurity/ClamAV signatures.
       - clamToolsdbd-log.py: Tool to create a valid configuration file.
 * (clamToolsd):
       - clamToolsd.py: Daemon to scheduled scans.
       - clamToolsd-config.py: Tool to create a valid configuration file.
       - clamToolsd-log.py: Tool to see the log file when daemon is running.

HOW TO INSTALL
--------------

 * Unix systems (GNU/Linux,*BSD, etc..)
 ======================================

   - Open the terminal and type the following comands:
   
     $ git https://github.com/clamsawd/clamTools.git
     $ cd clamTools
     # make install
     
   Note: You must install git, python3 & clamav previously.

 * Mac OS X
 ==========
 
   - Open the terminal and type the following comands:
     
     $ git clone https://github.com/clamsawd/clamTools.git
     $ cd clamTools
     # make -f makefile.osx
     
   Note: You must install git, python3 & clamav previously.
   
 * Windows
 =========
 
   - Install Python 3.x from https://www.python.org/.
   - Download https://github.com/clamsawd/clamTools/archive/master.zip
   - Unzip the package and rename it to 'clamTools'.
   - Copy the folder to 'C:\Program Files\'.
   - Double click on 'install.cmd'.
